---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Ornament Research">
  <style>
    .prose { max-width: 65ch; }
    h1 { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  </style>
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <h3>Cultural Startup</h3>
    <p>
      Master's research project exploring folklore ornaments, participatory design,
      and meaning-making in cultural identity.
    </p>
    <p>
      The project draws on <strong>folklore as a collective authorship model</strong>.
      Historically, national patterns emerged through distributed craft practices —
      distilling shared traits into ornament. This research proposes a contemporary
      analogue: a digitally mediated folklore process.
    </p>
    <p>
      Meaning is treated as dynamic and context-dependent. Authority over symbolic
      definition shifts from institutions to participants. The ornament becomes a
      living interface between individual perception and collective identity.
    </p>
    <h3>Question</h3>
    <p>Who defines the meaning of an ornament?</p>
    <ul>
      <li>What are the characteristics of the Belarusian national ornament?</li>
      <li>How can abstract ornamental motifs be described and interpreted?</li>
      <li>What can an act of reading ornament reveal about the people of Belarus?</li>
      <li>How to balance inclusion with the material constraints in national identity?</li>
      <li>How can the process of folklore authorship be replicated through digital technology?</li>
      <li>Is the final output a democratic average or a map of plural identities?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Goal</h3>
    <p>
      Explore how a crowdsourced, generative process can produce new ornamental
      variations reflecting diverse, present-day Belarusian perspectives — while
      maintaining cultural recognisability.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
